{"id":1491,"date":"2023-03-01T08:20:20","date_gmt":"2023-03-01T08:20:20","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/?p=1491"},"modified":"2023-03-01T08:20:20","modified_gmt":"2023-03-01T08:20:20","slug":"erasmus-mundus-program-emjmd-step-by-step-guide","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/erasmus-mundus-program-emjmd-step-by-step-guide\/","title":{"rendered":"Erasmus Mundus Program + EMJMD Step-by-Step Guide"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The Erasmus Mundus Program supports high-quality Master Courses and improves the attractiveness of European higher education for international students. This program offers several scholarships every year. Erasmus Mundus scholarships are granted to successful applicants until the end of the 2026 project. Read this article carefully if you need to know all about Erasmus Mundus&#8217;s joint Master&#8217;s degree and how to apply for it.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">In this guide:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">What is the Erasmus Mundus Joint Masters?<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">How to Apply for Erasmus Mundus Program<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Conclusion<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1644\" src=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/portrait-minded-man-pointing-his-mind-about-money-1.jpg\" alt=\"erasmus mundus program\" width=\"864\" height=\"576\" srcset=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/portrait-minded-man-pointing-his-mind-about-money-1.jpg 864w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/portrait-minded-man-pointing-his-mind-about-money-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/portrait-minded-man-pointing-his-mind-about-money-1-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 864px) 100vw, 864px\" \/><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"color: #333333;\">What is the Erasmus Mundus Joint Masters?<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The Erasmus Mundus Joint Master Degree or EMJMD is the perfect opportunity to learn and develop yourself through new experiences in several European countries.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The Erasmus Mundus program is a new initiative and part of the Erasmus+ Programs. Please do not confuse it with the Erasmus Mundus project in 2013.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The Erasmus Mundus program is a highly rated international study program offered by European higher education institutions. The accepted applicants spend the study period in at least two countries.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Many experts consider the Erasmus Mundus program one of the best Master&#8217;s scholarships ever. Not only is it open to any applicant in the world, but the scholarship covers the tuition fee, living costs, and health insurance.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The students receive much help from their universities, like finding housing or visa-related matters. Grantees of the Erasmus Mundus program are enrolled in anywhere from two to four universities during two years Master&#8217;s programs.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">They can choose to study in Europe and all parts of the world. They also benefit from language courses, free of charge in all countries.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">For each university in the Erasmus Mundus scholarship program, between 10 and 20 international students may receive a scholarship for each input session.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Erasmus Mundus program distinguishes two types of scholarship:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Program country scholarships are for:<\/span>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Students whose nationality is one of the Erasmus+ Program Countries<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Students from countries not part of the European Union or the EFTA or EEA.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Students that have not lived and have carried out their main activity in EU or EFTA or EEA countries for more than a year over the last five years.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Students that had never received an Erasmus+ scholarship for the Master&#8217;s study program.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Partner country scholarships are for:<\/span>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">All other students not eligible for Erasmus Mundus program country scholarship.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Subjects in Erasmus Mundus Program<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Every applicant is allowed to apply to a maximum of three programs per cycle at present. There are over 120 Erasmus Mundus Master&#8217;s courses, including:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Politics,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Chemistry,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Computing,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Smart Energy,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Human Rights,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Computer Science,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Engineering,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Economics,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Business,<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Each Master&#8217;s has a different consortium of universities that made it. It is important not to choose the Master&#8217;s based on the countries it takes place in, but following the applicant&#8217;s area of interest.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Find a Master&#8217;s in your area of interest that also takes you to many countries and gives you a lot of opportunities.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">For a complete list of Erasmus Mundus program degrees and the host countries, please check the official EMJMD page:<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><a style=\"color: #333333;\" href=\"https:\/\/erasmus-plus.ec.europa.eu\/\">https:\/\/erasmus-plus.ec.europa.eu\/<\/a><\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\">EMJMD Scholarships<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The most significant advantage of taking an EMJMD is that they cover the most costs. This student grant covers the participation costs, a monthly allowance for living costs, a contribution to travel, and installation costs.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Each grantee receives EUR 1000 per month for living costs during the 24 months program. The Erasmus Mundus Program provides full-time scholarships covering:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Monthly allowance,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Participation costs,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Insurance fee,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Travel fees.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Scholarship amounts may vary according to:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The level of studies,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The duration of studies,<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The scholar&#8217;s nationality.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The scholarship also contributes to travel, installation, and other costs in two installments.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The Euro culture participation costs EUR 9000 for EU students and 18000 for non-EU students, including health insurance coverage for 24 months.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The Erasmus Mundus program takes between 12 to 24 months to complete, which is very common for a Master&#8217;s Program.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Grantees have plenty of time to study in the university and explore Europe&#8217;s culture, landscapes, and ancient history.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Every applicant must be admitted to one of the given courses and then be selected for a scholarship to receive this financial support. The grant depends on the period of the program and the applicant&#8217;s country of origin.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"color: #333333;\">How to Apply for Erasmus Mundus Program<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The International Master in Global Markets and Local Creativities (GLOCAL) accepts applications from worldwide.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The GLOCAL program is dedicated to equality in activities. They accept applicants from all backgrounds and seek to create a learning environment free from discrimination and unfair treatment.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">This section is a step-by-step guide to applying for the Erasmus Mundus program grant. However, make sure to check the official Program page to discover the latest changes to this guide and the funding options available.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">if you need information about Top 10 Cheapest Cities for Living read this article:<\/span><\/p>\n<blockquote class=\"wp-embedded-content\" data-secret=\"N7NDk9dalT\"><p><a href=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/top-10-cheapest-cities-for-living\/\">Top 10 Cheapest Cities for Living<\/a><\/p><\/blockquote>\n<p><iframe class=\"wp-embedded-content\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts\" security=\"restricted\" style=\"position: absolute; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px);\" title=\"&#8220;Top 10 Cheapest Cities for Living&#8221; &#8212; Abroadin \" src=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/top-10-cheapest-cities-for-living\/embed\/#?secret=hVnPMTyKK1#?secret=N7NDk9dalT\" data-secret=\"N7NDk9dalT\" width=\"500\" height=\"282\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\"><\/iframe><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Step 1: Consider the Requirements<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Make sure to meet the entry requirements and eligibility criteria, which include:<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Scholarship students must have obtained a higher education degree or show an identified matching level of learning according to rules and legislation by the deadline.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">International students who have already obtained an Erasmus Mundus program or former Erasmus Mundus Master\/Doctoral Course holders are not qualified for an additional scholarship under the EMJMD action.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Students using an EMJMD scholarship cannot benefit from another EU grant while pursuing their Erasmus Mundus program studies.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">A differentiation between Program country students and partner country students is applied. No over 25 percent of the total number of scholarships available will be awarded to Program country students.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The monthly allowance is not given to scholarship holders from a Partner Country for the EMJMD periods exceeding three months spent in any Partner Country.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">International students from partner countries who have carried out their primary activity for more than a year in the last five years in one of the program countries are considered Program country applicants according to the 12-months rule.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Forgiven academic year student candidates can apply for a maximum of three joint Programs supported by the Erasmus Mundus program scholarships.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1642\" src=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/deadline-appointment-final-time-end-countdown-urgency-concept-1.jpg\" alt=\"erasmus mundus program\" width=\"750\" height=\"521\" srcset=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/deadline-appointment-final-time-end-countdown-urgency-concept-1.jpg 750w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/deadline-appointment-final-time-end-countdown-urgency-concept-1-300x208.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" \/><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Step 2: Follow the Deadlines<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Every application should be completed and offered on time to be considered. For more information, please take a look at the Selection Procedure &amp; Timetable page:<\/span><\/p>\n<blockquote class=\"wp-embedded-content\" data-secret=\"WFsohd9XEI\"><p><a href=\"https:\/\/globallocal-erasmusmundus.eu\/\">Home<\/a><\/p><\/blockquote>\n<p><iframe class=\"wp-embedded-content\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts\" security=\"restricted\" style=\"position: absolute; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px);\" title=\"&#8220;Home&#8221; &#8212; GLOCAL\" src=\"https:\/\/globallocal-erasmusmundus.eu\/embed\/#?secret=Mclyz1q59K#?secret=WFsohd9XEI\" data-secret=\"WFsohd9XEI\" width=\"500\" height=\"282\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\"><\/iframe><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Step 3: Choose the Study Pathway<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The applicant should choose the study track that best fits their interests and academic background. They also can only apply for one study track.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">GLOCAL is a 2-year full-time international master&#8217;s degree featuring a choice of 7 Study Tracks over a choice of seven Consortium Partner Universities, including:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">A: Global History &amp; Creative Industries (Glasgow, Barcelona, Rotterdam),<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">B: Global Markets &amp; Development (Glasgow, Barcelona, G\u00f6ttingen),<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">C: Sustainable Business Development (Glasgow, Barcelona, Los Andes),<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">D: Industrial Dynamics and Sustainability (Glasgow, Barcelona, Kyoto),<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">E: Institutional Change &amp; Creative Industries (Glasgow, Uppsala, Rotterdam),<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">F: Global Political Economy (Glasgow, Uppsala, G\u00f6ttingen),<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">G: Sustainability: Institutions &amp; Management (Glasgow, Uppsala, and Los Andes).<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">All students spend their first semester in Glasgow, the second semester in Barcelona or Uppsala, and then choose between Rotterdam, G\u00f6ttingen, Los Andes, or Kyoto for their third Consortium Partner University.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1641\" src=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/hand-with-pen-application-form-1.jpg\" alt=\"erasmus mundus program\" width=\"776\" height=\"518\" srcset=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/hand-with-pen-application-form-1.jpg 776w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/hand-with-pen-application-form-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/hand-with-pen-application-form-1-768x513.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 776px) 100vw, 776px\" \/><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Step 4: Fill out the Application Form<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The personal Statement section is your space to tell the Consortium why you are eligible to study GLOCAL and what your experience and background can bring to the program.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">All applicants worldwide, including those applying as self-funding students, must complete this:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Work out if you are a Program Country or Partner Country applicant;<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Complete, sign, and upload the Erasmus Mundus Scholarship application form as a PDF.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Before submitting the given form, make sure to spot your chosen study track. Your Statement indicates why your background and experience fit with GLOCAL.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Step 5: Check and Upload<\/span><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">All applications must be submitted in the online system. All applications are made online, and documents must be uploaded to the online application.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Ensure that you have uploaded all needed documents before submitting the online application. Here are some essential points to consider:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">You do not need to have your final degree certificate or English test results; these can be uploaded later.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Suppose you are completing the final year of your first degree or have yet to provide the required evidence of proficiency in English. In that case, you are considered for entry to the GLOCAL program. Still, you will not receive an Unconditional offer until we have received your final degree and English language test results. In such cases, you may have a conditional offer on you finishing your degree at the required grade and obtaining the required English language test results.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">You must submit this documentation before enrolling in the GLOCAL Program.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">In the end, click submit button. You receive a confirmation email containing login details and the applicant number. It confirms that the application was submitted successfully.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Conclusion<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The Erasmus Mundus program supports European top-quality Master Courses and enhances the visibility and attractiveness of European higher education.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">This scholarship is very intensive and highly competitive. Applicants compete with other top students with excellent profiles from all over the world.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">This article explained all you need about Erasmus Mundus and its application process. If any questions are left, ask them in the comments section.<\/span><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The Erasmus Mundus Program supports high-quality Master Courses and improves the attractiveness of European higher education for international students. This program offers several scholarships every year. Erasmus Mundus scholarships are granted to successful applicants until the end of the 2026 project. Read this article carefully if you need to know all about Erasmus Mundus&#8217;s joint [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":1643,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[121,1],"tags":[129,107,139,108,105,109,147,182],"class_list":["post-1491","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-scholarships","category-study-abroad","tag-europe","tag-europe-university","tag-international-student","tag-international-students","tag-study-europe","